==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[obiter dictum]]'': 

===Adjective===
# {{law}} Used as an elipse for [[obiter dictum]]. A statement from the [[bench]] commenting on a point of law which is  not necessary for the judgment at hand and therefore has no judicial weight, as opposed to [[ratio decidendi]].

====Synonyms====
*[[obiter dictum]]

